refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;

 DOMElementDOMDocument::createElement
 stringname
 stringvalue



 This function creates a new instance of class
 DOMElement. &dom.node.inserted;

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 Returns a new instance of class DOMElement or &false;
 if an error occured.

&reftitle.errors;




   DOM_INVALID_CHARACTER_ERR



     Raised if name contains an invalid character.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Creating a new element and inserting it as root


<?php

$dom = new DOMDocument('1.0', 'iso-8859-1');

$element = $dom->createElement('test', 'This is the root element!');

// We insert the new element as root (child of the document)
$dom->appendChild($element);

echo $dom->saveXML();
?>


    &example.outputs;


<?xml version="1.0" encoding="iso-8859-1"?>
<test>This is the root element!</test>

&reftitle.notes;



  To create a text node with escaping support use
  DOMDocument::createTextElement.
